# ==========================================================
# üì± ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC CONFIGS
# ==========================================================
#
# Development:
#   - Use your Supabase project's development URL
#   - Can enable debug logs temporarily
#   - EXPO_PUBLIC_DEBUG_MODE=true (optional)
#   - EXPO_PUBLIC_USE_MOCK_DATA=true (for testing)
#
# Staging:
#   - Use staging Supabase project
#   - Keep mock data disabled
#   - EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=staging
#
# Production:
#   - Use production Supabase project
#   - All debug/mock flags must be false
#   - EXPO_PUBLIC_PRODUCTION_BUILD=true
#   - Deploy via EAS Build with production secrets
#
# ==========================================================
# üöÄ DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# ==========================================================
#
# Local Development:
#   1. Copy this file to .env
#   2. Fill in your critical variables (Supabase & Stripe)
#   3. Run: npx expo start
#
# EAS Build:
#   1. Set secrets in EAS: eas secret:push
#   2. Build: eas build --platform android --profile production
#
# CI/CD:
#   1. Set as repository secrets in GitHub
#   2. Workflow will validate configuration
#
# Quick Validation:
#   Run: npm run validate:env (if available)
